    TagVLiteralOrFilter.TagVILiteralOrFilter

    public class TagVLiteralOrFilter
extends TagVFilter
    A filter that lets the user list one or more explicit strings that should be included in a result set for aggregation.
    从以下版本开始:
    2.2

        public TagVLiteralOrFilter(String tagk,

        The default Ctor that disables case insensitivity

                           String filter,
                           boolean case_insensitive)
        A ctor that allows enabling case insensitivity
        参数:
        tagk - The tag key to associate with this filter
        filter - The filter to match on
        case_insensitive - Whether or not to match on case
        抛出:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the tagk or filter were empty or null

      • match

        public com.stumbleupon.async.Deferred<Boolean> match(Map<String,String> tags)
        从类复制的说明: TagVFilter
        Looks up the tag key in the given map and determines if the filter matches or not. If the tag key doesn't exist in the tag map, then the match fails.
        指定者:
        match 在类中 TagVFilter
        参数:
        tags - The tag map to use for looking up the value for the tagk
        返回:
        True if the tag value matches, false if it doesn't.

      • resolveTagkName

        public com.stumbleupon.async.Deferred<byte[]> resolveTagkName(TSDB tsdb)
        Overridden here so that we can resolve the literal values if we don't have too many of them AND we're not searching with case insensitivity.
        覆盖:
        resolveTagkName 在类中 TagVFilter
        参数:
        tsdb - The TSDB to use for the lookup
        返回:

        public String getType()
        从类复制的说明: TagVFilter
        The name of this filter as used in queries. When used in URL queries the value will be in parentheses, e.g. filter(<exp>) The name will also be lowercased before storing it in the lookup map.
